'''Sources''': Boeing 747 specifications,&lt;ref name=specs&gt;[http://www.boeing.com/commercial/747family/specs.html &quot;747 specifications&quot;], ''The Boeing Company''. Retrieved 16 December 2007.&lt;/ref&gt; 747 airport planning report,&lt;ref name=plan&gt;[http://www.boeing.com/commercial/airports/747.htm &quot;747 Airplane Characteristics for Airport Planning.&quot;] ''The Boeing Company''. Retrieved: December 15, 2007.&lt;/ref&gt; 747-8 airport brochure&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.boeing.com/commercial/airports/acaps/7478brochure.pdf &quot;Preliminary 747-8 Airport Compatibility.&quot;] ''The Boeing Company''. Retrieved: July 8, 2009.&lt;/ref&gt;

* The 747 parasitic drag, C&lt;sub&gt;DP&lt;/sub&gt;, is 0.022, and the wing area is {{convert|5500|sqft|m2|0|}}, so that ''f'' equals about 121&amp;nbsp;sq ft or 11.2&amp;nbsp;m². The [[parasitic drag]] is given by ''½ f ρ&lt;sub&gt;air&lt;/sub&gt; v²'' in which ''f'' is the product of drag coefficient C&lt;sub&gt;Dp&lt;/sub&gt; and the wing area.&lt;ref&gt;[http://selair.selkirk.bc.ca/aerodynamics1/Drag/Page4.html &quot;Calculating and Plotting Parasite Drag.&quot;] ''Aerodynamics Text''. Retrieved: December 17, 2007.&lt;/ref&gt;

* &quot;Required runway&quot; length allows for emergency factors. Actual takeoff distances will normally be considerably shorter than those listed here. See [[Balanced field takeoff]].

==Notable appearances in media==
{{Main|Aircraft in fiction#Boeing 747|l1=Aircraft in fiction (Boeing 747)}}

Following its debut, the 747 rapidly achieved [[Cultural icon|iconic]] status, [[G-BDXJ|appearing]] in various film productions such as the [[Airport 1975|''Airport'' series]] of disaster films, ''[[Air Force One (film)|Air Force One]]'' and ''[[Executive Decision]]''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.ram.org/ramblings/movies/executive_decision.html &quot;Executive Decision.&quot;] ''Movie Ramblings''. Retrieved: December 17, 2007.&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/air_force_one/ &quot;Air Force One.&quot;] ''Rotten Tomatoes''. Retrieved: December 17, 2007.&lt;/ref&gt; The 747 was also referenced in the [[Earth, Wind &amp; Fire]] song ''[[Let's Groove]]''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.stlyrics.com/lyrics/thewaterboy/letsgroove.htm &quot;Let's Groove.&quot;] ''stlyrics.com.'' Retrieved: September 6, 2010.&lt;/ref&gt;

