      <text xml:space="preserve">'''Burgundian''' can refer to any of the following:

*[[Burgundians]], an East Germanic tribe, who first appear in history in South East Europe. Later Burgundians colonised the area of Gaul that is now known as Burgundy (French Bourgogne).
*The Old [[Burgundian language (Germanic)|Burgundian language]], an East Germanic language spoken by the Burgundians.
*The Modern [[Burgundian language (Oïl)|Burgundian language]], an Oïl language also known as Bourguignon spoken in the region of Burgundy. It is one of the Dialects or Languages of France. Sometimes Franc-Comtois is referred to as part of the Burgundian group.
*Someone from [[Burgundy (region)|Burgundy]].
*[[Burgundian (party)]], a political faction in early 15th century during the Hundred Years' War.

